BEGIN_TEXT

If the determinant of a \($n \times $n\) matrix \(A\) is \(\det \,(A)=$a\), and the matrix \(C\) is obtained from \(A\) by
swapping the $which[$tag1] and $which[$tag2] $rc[$tag3], then \(\det \,(C)= \) \{ans_rule(5)\}.  

END_TEXT

ANS(num_cmp($b));

